msgid ""
"This is only meaningful if the underlying distribution really has a fourth "
"moment.  The kurtosis is offset by three such that a normal distribution "
"will have zero kurtosis."
msgstr ""
"Dette er kun meningsfuldt hvis den underliggende fordeling virkelig har et "
"fjerde moment. Kurtosen er forskudt med tre således at en normalfordeling "
"vil have nul kurtose."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2123
msgid ""
"If fewer than four numbers are given or all of them are equal this function "
"returns a #DIV/0! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der gives færre end fire tal eller alle er ens returnerer denne "
"funktion en #DIV/0!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2147
msgid "KURTP:population kurtosis of a data set"
msgstr "KURTP:Populations-kurtosis for et datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2151
msgid ""
"If fewer than two numbers are given or all of them are equal this function "
"returns a #DIV/0! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der gives færre end to tal eller alle er ens returnerer denne funktion "
"en #DIV/0!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2173
msgid "AVEDEV:average of the absolute deviations of a data set"
msgstr "AVEDEV:Gennemsnit af de absolutte afvigelser i et datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2198
msgid "DEVSQ:sum of squares of deviations of a data set"
msgstr "DEVSQ:Sum af kvadrerede afvigelser i et datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2224
msgid "FISHER:Fisher transformation"
msgstr "FISHER:Fisher-transformation"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2226
msgid "If @{x} is not a number, this function returns a #VALUE! error."
msgstr "Hvis @{x} ikke er et tal, så returnerer denne funktion fejlen #VÆRDI!"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2227
msgid "If @{x} <= -1 or @{x} >= 1, this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{x} <= -1 eller @{x} >= 1, så returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2248
msgid ""
"POISSON:probability mass or cumulative distribution function of the Poisson "
"distribution"
msgstr ""
"POISSON:Sandsynlighedsmasse eller kumulativ fordelingsfunktion for Poisson-"
"fordelingen"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2249
msgid "x:number of events"
msgstr "x:antal hændelser"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2252
msgid "If @{x} is a non-integer it is truncated."
msgstr "Hvis @{x} ikke er et heltal, afkortes den."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2254
msgid "If @{mean} <= 0 POISSON returns the #NUM! error."
msgstr "Hvis @{mean} <= 0, så returnerer POISSON fejlen #TAL!"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2280
msgid "PEARSON:Pearson correlation coefficient of the paired set of data"
msgstr "PEARSON:Pearson-korrelationskoefficient for det parrede datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2281 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2301
msgid "array1:first component values"
msgstr "array1:første komponentværdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2282 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2302
msgid "array2:second component values"
msgstr "array2:anden komponentværdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2300
msgid ""
"RSQ:square of the Pearson correlation coefficient of the paired set of data"
msgstr ""
"RSQ:Kvadratet på Pearson-korrelationskoefficienten for det parrede datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2325
msgid "MEDIAN:median of a data set"
msgstr "MEDIAN:Median for et datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2329
msgid ""
"If even numbers are given MEDIAN returns the average of the two numbers in "
"the center."
msgstr ""
"Hvis der gives lige tal returnerer MEDIAN gennemsnittet af de to tal i "
"midten."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2334
msgid "wiki:en:Median"
msgstr ""

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2335
msgid "wolfram:StatisticalMedian.html"
msgstr ""

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2356
msgid "SSMEDIAN:median for grouped data"
msgstr "SSMEDIAN:Median for grupperede data"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2357
msgid "array:data set"
msgstr "array:datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2358
msgid "interval:length of each grouping interval, defaults to 1"
msgstr "interval:længde for hvert grupperingsinterval, standardværdi er 1"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2359
msgid ""
"The data are assumed to be grouped into intervals of width @{interval}. Each "
"data point in @{array} is the midpoint of the interval containing the true "
"value. The median is calculated by interpolation within the median interval "
"(the interval containing the median value), assuming that the true values "
"within that interval are distributed uniformly:\n"
"median = L + @{interval}*(N/2 - CF)/F\n"
"where:\n"
"L = the lower limit of the median interval\n"
"N = the total number of data points\n"
"CF = the number of data points below the median interval\n"
"F = the number of data points in the median interval"
msgstr ""
"Dataene antages at være grupperet i intervaller med bredde @{interval}. "
"Hvert datapunkt i @{array} er midtpunktet af intervallet der indeholder den "
"sande værdi. Medianen beregnes ved interpolation inden for medianintervallet "
"(intervallet der indeholder medianværdien), under antagelse af at de sande "
"værdier inden for det interval er fordelt ensartet:\n"
"median = L + @{interval}*(N/2 - CF)/F\n"
"hvor:\n"
"L = den nedre grænse for medianintervallet\n"
"N = det samlede antal datapunkter\n"
"CF = antallet af datapunkter under medianintervallet\n"
"F = antallet af datapunkter i medianintervallet"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2370 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3157
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3199 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3244
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3287
msgid "If @{array} is empty, this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr "Hvis @{array} er tom, så returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2371
msgid ""
"If @{interval} <= 0, this function returns a #NUM! error. SSMEDIAN does not "
"check whether the data points are at least @{interval} apart."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{interval} <= 0, returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl. SSMEDIAN "
"kontrollerer ikke om datapunkterne er mindst @{interval} fra hinanden."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2458
msgid "LARGE:@{k}-th largest value in a data set"
msgstr "LARGE:@{k}'ende største værdi i et datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2459 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2517
msgid "data:data set"
msgstr "data:datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2460 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2518
msgid "k:which value to find"
msgstr "k:hvilken værdi der skal findes"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2461 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2519
msgid "If data set is empty this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr "Hvis datasættet er tomt returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2462 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2520
msgid ""
"If @{k} <= 0 or @{k} is greater than the number of data items given this "
"function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{k} <= 0 eller @{k} er større end antallet af givne dataelementer "
"returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2467
msgid "Then LARGE(A1:A5,2) equals 25.9. LARGE(A1:A5,4) equals 17.3."
msgstr "Så er LARGE(A1:A5,2) lig med 25,9. LARGE(A1:A5,4) er lig med 17,3."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2516
msgid "SMALL:@{k}-th smallest value in a data set"
msgstr "SMALL:@{k}'ende mindste værdi i et datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2525
msgid "Then SMALL(A1:A5,2) equals 17.3. SMALL(A1:A5,4) equals 25.9."
msgstr "Så er SMALL(A1:A5,2) lig med 17,3. SMALL(A1:A5,4) er lig med 25,9."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2559
msgid ""
"PROB:probability of an interval for a discrete (and finite) probability "
"distribution"
msgstr ""
"PROB:Sandsynlighed for et interval for en diskret (og endelig) "
"sandsynlighedsfordeling"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2560
msgid "x_range:possible values"
msgstr "x_range:mulige værdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2561
msgid "prob_range:probabilities of the corresponding values"
msgstr "prob_range:sandsynligheder for de tilsvarende værdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2562
msgid "lower_limit:lower interval limit"
msgstr "lower_limit:nedre intervalgrænse"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2563
msgid "upper_limit:upper interval limit, defaults to @{lower_limit}"
msgstr "upper_limit:øvre intervalgrænse, standardværdi er @{lower_limit}"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2564
msgid ""
"If the sum of the probabilities in @{prob_range} is not equal to 1 this "
"function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis summen af sandsynlighederne i @{prob_range} ikke er lig med 1 "
"returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2566
msgid ""
"If any value in @{prob_range} is <=0 or > 1, this function returns a #NUM! "
"error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis nogen værdi i @{prob_range} er <=0 eller > 1, returnerer denne funktion "
"en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2568
msgid ""
"If @{x_range} and @{prob_range} contain a different number of data entries, "
"this function returns a #N/A error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{x_range} og @{prob_range} indeholder forskellige antal dataposter, "
"returnerer denne funktion en #N/A-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2643
msgid "STEYX:standard error of the predicted y-value in the regression"
msgstr "STEYX:Standardfejl for den forudsagte y-værdi i regressionen"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2644 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3941
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4055 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4297
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4393 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4497
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4556 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4608
msgid "known_ys:known y-values"
msgstr "known_ys:kendte y-værdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2645 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4056
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4498 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4557
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4609
msgid "known_xs:known x-values"
msgstr "known_xs:kendte x-værdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2646
msgid ""
"If @{known_ys} and @{known_xs} are empty or have a different number of "
"arguments then this function returns a #N/A error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{known_ys} og @{known_xs} er tomme eller har forskellige antal "
"argumenter så returnerer denne funktion en #N/A-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2652
msgid "Then STEYX(A1:A5,B1:B5) equals 1.101509979."
msgstr "Så er STEYX(A1:A5,B1:B5) lig med 1,101509979."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2696
msgid ""
"ZTEST:the probability of observing a sample mean as large as or larger than "
"the mean of the given sample"
msgstr ""
"ZTEST:Sandsynligheden for at observere en stikprøvemiddelværdi lige så stor "
"eller større end middelværdien af den givne stikprøve"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2698
msgid "ref:data set (sample)"
msgstr "ref:datasæt (stikprøve)"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2699
msgid "x:population mean"
msgstr "x:populationsmiddelværdi"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2700
msgid ""
"stddev:population standard deviation, defaults to the sample standard "
"deviation"
msgstr ""
"stddev:populations-standardafvigelse, standardværdi er stikprøvens "
"standardafvigelse"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2701
msgid ""
"ZTEST calculates the probability of observing a sample mean as large as or "
"larger than the mean of the given sample for samples drawn from a normal "
"distribution with mean @{x} and standard deviation @{stddev}."
msgstr ""
"ZTEST beregner sandsynligheden for at observere en stikprøvemiddelværdi lige "
"så stor eller større end middelværdien af den givne stikprøve for stikprøver "
"trukket fra en normalfordeling med middelværdi @{x} og standardafvigelse "
"@{stddev}."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2704
msgid ""
"If @{ref} contains less than two data items ZTEST returns #DIV/0! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{ref} indeholder færre end to dataelementer returnerer ZTEST #DIV/0!-"
"fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2710
msgid "Then ZTEST(A1:A5,20) equals 0.254717826."
msgstr "Så er ZTEST(A1:A5,20) lig med 0,254717826."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2761
msgid "AVERAGEA:average of all the values and cells"
msgstr "AVERAGEA:Gennemsnit af alle værdier og celler"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2786
msgid ""
"MAXA:largest value, with negative numbers considered smaller than positive "
"numbers"
msgstr ""
"MAXA:Største værdi, hvor negative tal betragtes som mindre end positive tal"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2812
msgid ""
"MINA:smallest value, with negative numbers considered smaller than positive "
"numbers"
msgstr ""
"MINA:Mindste værdi, hvor negative tal betragtes som mindre end positive tal"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2838
msgid "VARA:sample variance of the given sample"
msgstr "VARA:Stikprøve-varians for den givne stikprøve"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2841
msgid "VARA is also known as the N-1-variance."
msgstr "VARA er også kendt som N-1-variansen."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2842
msgid "To get the true variance of a complete population use VARPA."
msgstr "For at få den sande varians af en hel population skal du bruge VARPA."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2868
msgid "VARPA:variance of an entire population"
msgstr "VARPA:Varians for en hel population"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2871
msgid "VARPA is also known as the N-variance."
msgstr "VARPA er også kendt som N-variansen."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2894
msgid "STDEVA:sample standard deviation of the given sample"
msgstr "STDEVA:Stikprøve-standardafvigelse for den givne stikprøve"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2898
msgid "STDEVA is also known as the N-1-standard deviation."
msgstr "STDEVA er også kendt som N-1-standardafvigelsen."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2899
msgid ""
"To obtain the population standard deviation of a whole population use "
"STDEVPA."
msgstr ""
"For at få populations-standardafvigelsen af en hel population skal du bruge "
"STDEVPA."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2923
msgid "STDEVPA:population standard deviation of an entire population"
msgstr "STDEVPA:Populations-standardafvigelse for en hel population"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2949
msgid ""
"PERCENTRANK:rank of a data point in a data set (Hyndman-Fan method 7: N-1 "
"basis)"
msgstr ""
"PERCENTRANK:Rang af et datapunkt i et datasæt (Hyndman-Fan metode 7: N-1 "
"basis)"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2950 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3054
msgid "array:range of numeric values"
msgstr "array:interval af numeriske værdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2951 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3055
msgid "x:data point to be ranked"
msgstr "x:datapunkt der skal rangeres"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2952 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3056
msgid "significance:number of significant digits, defaults to 3"
msgstr "significance:antal betydende cifre, standardværdi er 3"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2953 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3057
msgid ""
"If @{array} contains no data points, this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{array} ikke indeholder nogen datapunkter, returnerer denne funktion "
"en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2955 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3059
msgid ""
"If @{significance} is less than one, this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{significance} er mindre end én, returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-"
"fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2957 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3061
msgid ""
"If @{x} exceeds the largest value or is less than the smallest value in "
"@{array}, this function returns an #N/A error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{x} overstiger den største værdi eller er mindre end den mindste værdi "
"i @{array}, returnerer denne funktion en #N/A-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:2959 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3063
msgid ""
"If @{x} does not match any of the values in @{array} or @{x} matches more "
"than once, this function interpolates the returned value."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{x} ikke matcher nogen af værdierne i @{array} eller @{x} matcher mere "
"end én gang, interpolerer denne funktion den returnerede værdi."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3053
msgid ""
"PERCENTRANK.EXC:rank of a data point in a data set (Hyndman-Fan method 6: "
"N+1 basis)"
msgstr ""
"PERCENTRANK.EXC:Rang af et datapunkt i et datasæt (Hyndman-Fan metode 6: N+1 "
"basis)"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3154
msgid ""
"PERCENTILE:determines the 100*@{k}-th percentile of the given data points "
"(Hyndman-Fan method 7: N-1 basis)"
msgstr ""
"PERCENTILE:Bestemmer den 100*@{k}'te percentil af de givne datapunkter "
"(Hyndman-Fan metode 7: N-1 basis)"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3155 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3197
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3242 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3285
msgid "array:data points"
msgstr "array:datapunkter"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3156 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3198
msgid "k:which percentile to calculate"
msgstr "k:hvilken percentil der skal beregnes"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3158 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3200
msgid "If @{k} < 0 or @{k} > 1, this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{k} < 0 eller @{k} > 1, så returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3161
msgid "Then PERCENTILE(A1:A5,0.42) equals 20.02."
msgstr "Så er PERCENTILE(A1:A5,0.42) lig med 20,02."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3196
msgid ""
"PERCENTILE.EXC:determines the 100*@{k}-th percentile of the given data "
"points (Hyndman-Fan method 6: N+1 basis)"
msgstr ""
"PERCENTILE.EXC:Bestemmer den 100*@{k}'te percentil af de givne datapunkter "
"(Hyndman-Fan metode 6: N+1 basis)"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3203
msgid "Then PERCENTILE.EXC(A1:A5,0.42) equals 20.02."
msgstr "Så er PERCENTILE.EXC(A1:A5,0.42) lig med 20,02."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3241
msgid ""
"QUARTILE:the @{quart}-th quartile of the data points (Hyndman-Fan method 7: "
"N-1 basis)"
msgstr ""
"QUARTILE:Den @{quart}'te kvartil af datapunkterne (Hyndman-Fan metode 7: N-1 "
"basis)"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3243
msgid "quart:a number from 0 to 4, indicating which quartile to calculate"
msgstr ""
"quart:et tal fra 0 til 4, der angiver hvilken kvartil der skal beregnes"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3245 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3288
msgid ""
"If @{quart} < 0 or @{quart} > 4, this function returns a #NUM! error. If "
"@{quart} = 0, the smallest value of @{array} to be returned."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{quart} < 0 eller @{quart} > 4, returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-"
"fejl. Hvis @{quart} = 0, returneres den mindste værdi af @{array}."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3246 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3289
msgid "If @{quart} is not an integer, it is truncated."
msgstr "Hvis @{quart} ikke er et heltal, afkortes den."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3249
msgid "Then QUARTILE(A1:A5,1) equals 17.3."
msgstr "Så er QUARTILE(A1:A5,1) lig med 17,3."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3284
msgid ""
"QUARTILE.EXC:the @{quart}-th quartile of the data points (Hyndman-Fan method "
"6: N+1 basis)"
msgstr ""
"QUARTILE.EXC:Den @{quart}'te kvartil af datapunkterne (Hyndman-Fan metode 6: "
"N+1 basis)"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3286
msgid "quart:a number from 1 to 3, indicating which quartile to calculate"
msgstr ""
"quart:et tal fra 1 til 3, der angiver hvilken kvartil der skal beregnes"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3292
msgid "Then QUARTILE.EXC(A1:A5,1) equals 14.35."
msgstr "Så er QUARTILE.EXC(A1:A5,1) lig med 14,35."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3330
msgid ""
"FTEST:p-value for the two-tailed hypothesis test comparing the variances of "
"two populations"
msgstr ""
"FTEST:P-værdi for den tohalede hypotesetest der sammenligner varianserne af "
"to populationer"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3332 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3389
msgid "array1:sample from the first population"
msgstr "array1:stikprøve fra den første population"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3333 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3390
msgid "array2:sample from the second population"
msgstr "array2:stikprøve fra den anden population"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3338
msgid "Then FTEST(A1:A5,B1:B5) equals 0.510815017."
msgstr "Så er FTEST(A1:A5,B1:B5) lig med 0,510815017."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3387
msgid ""
"TTEST:p-value for a hypothesis test comparing the means of two populations "
"using the Student t-distribution"
msgstr ""
"TTEST:P-værdi for en hypotesetest der sammenligner middelværdierne af to "
"populationer ved hjælp af Student-t-fordelingen"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3391
msgid "tails:number of tails to consider"
msgstr "tails:antal haler der skal overvejes"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3392
msgid ""
"type:Type of test to perform. 1 indicates a test for paired variables, 2 a "
"test of unpaired variables with equal variances, and 3 a test of unpaired "
"variables with unequal variances"
msgstr ""
"type:Type af test der skal udføres. 1 angiver en test for parrede variable, "
"2 en test af uparrede variable med lige varianser, og 3 en test af uparrede "
"variable med ulige varianser"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3395
msgid ""
"If the data sets contain a different number of data points and the test is "
"paired (@{type} one), TTEST returns the #N/A error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis datasættene indeholder forskellige antal datapunkter og testen er "
"parret (@{type} én), returnerer TTEST #N/A-fejlen."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3397
msgid "@{tails} and @{type} are truncated to integers."
msgstr "@{tails} og @{type} afkortes til heltal."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3398
msgid "If @{tails} is not one or two, this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{tails} ikke er et eller to, så returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-"
"fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3399
msgid ""
"If @{type} is any other than one, two, or three, this function returns a "
"#NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{type} er andre end én, to eller tre, returnerer denne funktion en "
"#TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3404
msgid ""
"Then TTEST(A1:A5,B1:B5,1,1) equals 0.003127619. TTEST(A1:A5,B1:B5,2,1) "
"equals 0.006255239. TTEST(A1:A5,B1:B5,1,2) equals 0.111804322. TTEST(A1:A5,"
"B1:B5,1,3) equals 0.113821797."
msgstr ""
"Så er TTEST(A1:A5,B1:B5,1,1) lig med 0,003127619. TTEST(A1:A5,B1:B5,2,1) er "
"lig med 0,006255239. TTEST(A1:A5,B1:B5,1,2) er lig med 0,111804322. TTEST(A1:"
"A5,B1:B5,1,3) er lig med 0,113821797."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3562
msgid "FREQUENCY:frequency table"
msgstr "FREQUENCY:Frekvenståbel"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3563
msgid "data_array:data values"
msgstr "data_array:dataværdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3564
msgid "bins_array:array of cutoff values"
msgstr "bins_array:matrix af afskæringsværdier"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3565
msgid "The results are given as an array."
msgstr "Resultaterne gives som en matrix."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3566
msgid ""
"If the @{bins_array} is empty, this function returns the number of data "
"points in @{data_array}."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{bins_array} er tom, returnerer denne funktion antallet af datapunkter "
"i @{data_array}."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3629
msgid "LEVERAGE:calculate regression leverage"
msgstr "LEVERAGE:Beregn regressionsleverage"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3632
msgid ""
"Returns the diagonal of @{A} (@{A}^T @{A})^-1 @{A}^T as a column vector."
msgstr ""
"Returnerer diagonalen af @{A} (@{A}^T @{A})^-1 @{A}^T som en kolonnevektor."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3633
msgid "If the matrix is singular, #VALUE! is returned."
msgstr "Hvis matrixen er singulær, returneres #VÆRDI!"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3836
msgid "LINEST:multiple linear regression coefficients and statistics"
msgstr "LINEST:Multiple lineære regressionskoefficienter og statistik"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3837 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4150
msgid "known_ys:vector of values of dependent variable"
msgstr "known_ys:vektor af værdier for den afhængige variabel"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3838 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4151
msgid ""
"known_xs:array of values of independent variables, defaults to a single "
"vector {1,…,n}"
msgstr ""
"known_xs:matrix af værdier af uafhængige variable, standardværdi er en "
"enkelt vektor {1,…,n}"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3839 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3943
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4153 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4299
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4396
msgid "affine:if true, the model contains a constant term, defaults to true"
msgstr ""
"affine:hvis sand, indeholder modellen et konstant led, standardværdi er sand"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3840
msgid ""
"stats:if true, some additional statistics are provided, defaults to false"
msgstr ""
"stats:hvis sand, gives nogle yderligere statistikker, standardværdi er falsk"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3841
msgid ""
"This function returns an array with the first row giving the regression "
"coefficients for the independent variables x_m, x_(m-1),…,x_2, x_1 followed "
"by the y-intercept if @{affine} is true."
msgstr ""
"Denne funktion returnerer en matrix hvor den første række giver "
"regressionskoefficienterne for de uafhængige variable x_m, x_(m-1),…,x_2, "
"x_1 efterfulgt af y-akseskæringen hvis @{affine} er sand."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3844
msgid ""
"If @{stats} is true, the second row contains the corresponding standard "
"errors of the regression coefficients. In this case, the third row contains "
"the R^2 value and the standard error for the predicted value. The fourth row "
"contains the observed F value and its degrees of freedom. Finally, the fifth "
"row contains the regression sum of squares and the residual sum of squares."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{stats} er sand, indeholder den anden række de tilsvarende "
"standardfejl for regressionskoefficienterne. I dette tilfælde indeholder den "
"tredje række R^2-værdien og standardfejlen for den forudsagte værdi. Den "
"fjerde række indeholder den observerede F-værdi og dens frihedsgrader. "
"Endelig indeholder den femte række regressionens sum af kvadrater og "
"residual sum af kvadrater."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3851
msgid ""
"If @{affine} is false, R^2 is the uncentered version of the coefficient of "
"determination; that is the proportion of the sum of squares explained by the "
"model."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{affine} er falsk, er R^2 den ucentrerede version af "
"determinationskoefficienten; det vil sige andelen af sum af kvadrater "
"forklaret af modellen."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3854 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4154
msgid ""
"If the length of @{known_ys} does not match the corresponding length of "
"@{known_xs}, this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis længden af @{known_ys} ikke matcher den tilsvarende længde af "
"@{known_xs}, returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3940
msgid "LOGREG:the logarithmic regression"
msgstr "LOGREG:Den logaritmiske regression"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3942 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4394
msgid "known_xs:known x-values; defaults to the array {1, 2, 3, …}"
msgstr "known_xs:kendte x-værdier; standardværdi er matrixen {1, 2, 3, …}"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3944 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4300
msgid ""
"stat:if true, extra statistical information will be returned; defaults to "
"FALSE"
msgstr ""
"stat:hvis sand, vil ekstra statistisk information blive returneret; "
"standardværdi er FALSK"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3945
msgid ""
"LOGREG function transforms your x's to z=ln(x) and applies the “least "
"squares” method to fit the linear equation y = m * z + b to your y's and z's "
"--- equivalent to fitting the equation y = m * ln(x) + b to y's and x's. "
"LOGREG returns an array having two columns and one row. m is given in the "
"first column and b in the second."
msgstr ""
"LOGREG-funktionen transformerer dine x'er til z=ln(x) og anvender \"mindste "
"kvadraters\" metode til at tilpasse den lineære ligning y = m * z + b til "
"dine y'er og z'er --- ækvivalent med at tilpasse ligningen y = m * ln(x) + b "
"til y'er og x'er. LOGREG returnerer en matrix med to kolonner og én række. m "
"gives i den første kolonne og b i den anden."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3953
msgid ""
"Any extra statistical information is written below m and b in the result "
"array.  This extra statistical information consists of four rows of data:  "
"In the first row the standard error values for the coefficients m, b are "
"given.  The second row contains the square of R and the standard error for "
"the y estimate. The third row contains the F-observed value and the degrees "
"of freedom.  The last row contains the regression sum of squares and the "
"residual sum of squares. The default of @{stat} is FALSE."
msgstr ""
"Eventuel ekstra statistisk information skrives under m og b i "
"resultatmatrixen. Denne ekstra statistiske information består af fire rækker "
"af data: I den første række gives standardfejlværdierne for koefficienterne "
"m, b. Den anden række indeholder kvadratet af R og standardfejlen for y-"
"estimatet. Den tredje række indeholder F-observeret værdi og "
"frihedsgraderne. Den sidste række indeholder regressionens sum af kvadrater "
"og residual sum af kvadrater. Standardværdien for @{stat} er FALSK."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:3962 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4315
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4405
msgid ""
"If @{known_ys} and @{known_xs} have unequal number of data points, this "
"function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{known_ys} og @{known_xs} har ulige antal datapunkter, returnerer "
"denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4054
msgid "LOGFIT:logarithmic least square fit (using a trial and error method)"
msgstr ""
"LOGFIT:Logaritmisk mindste kvadraters tilpasning (ved hjælp af forsøg-og-"
"fejl-metode)"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4058
msgid ""
"LOGFIT function applies the “least squares” method to fit the logarithmic "
"equation y = a + b * ln(sign * (x - c)) ,   sign = +1 or -1 to your data. "
"The graph of the equation is a logarithmic curve moved horizontally by c and "
"possibly mirrored across the y-axis (if sign = -1)."
msgstr ""
"LOGFIT-funktionen anvender \"mindste kvadraters\" metode til at tilpasse den "
"logaritmiske ligning y = a + b * ln(sign * (x - c)) , sign = +1 eller -1 til "
"dine data. Grafen for ligningen er en logaritmisk kurve flyttet vandret med "
"c og muligvis spejlet over y-aksen (hvis sign = -1)."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4064
msgid ""
"LOGFIT returns an array having five columns and one row. `Sign' is given in "
"the first column, `a', `b', and `c' are given in columns 2 to 4. Column 5 "
"holds the sum of squared residuals."
msgstr ""
"LOGFIT returnerer en matrix med fem kolonner og én række. `Sign' gives i den "
"første kolonne, `a', `b' og `c' gives i kolonnerne 2 til 4. Kolonne 5 "
"indeholder summen af kvadrerede residualer."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4068
msgid ""
"An error is returned when there are less than 3 different x's or y's, or "
"when the shape of the point cloud is too different from a ``logarithmic'' "
"one."
msgstr ""
"En fejl returneres når der er færre end 3 forskellige x'er eller y'er, eller "
"når formen af punktskyen er for forskellig fra en ``logaritmisk'' én."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4071
msgid ""
"You can use the above formula = a + b * ln(sign * (x - c)) or rearrange it "
"to = (exp((y - a) / b)) / sign + c to compute unknown y's or x's, "
"respectively."
msgstr ""
"Du kan bruge ovenstående formel = a + b * ln(sign * (x - c)) eller "
"omarrangere den til = (exp((y - a) / b)) / sign + c for at beregne ukendte "
"y'er eller x'er henholdsvis."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4076
msgid ""
"This is non-linear fitting by trial-and-error. The accuracy of `c' is: width "
"of x-range -> rounded to the next smaller (10^integer), times 0.000001. "
"There might be cases in which the returned fit is not the best possible."
msgstr ""
"Dette er ikke-lineær tilpasning ved trial-and-error. Nøjagtigheden af `c' "
"er: bredden af x-interval -> rundet til næste mindre (10^heltal), gange "
"0,000001. Der kan være tilfælde hvor den returnerede tilpasning ikke er den "
"bedst mulige."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4149
msgid ""
"TREND:estimates future values of a given data set using a least squares "
"approximation"
msgstr ""
"TREND:Estimerer fremtidige værdier af et givet datasæt ved hjælp af en "
"mindste kvadraters approksimation"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4152
msgid ""
"new_xs:array of x-values for which to estimate the y-values; defaults to "
"@{known_xs}"
msgstr ""
"new_xs:matrix af x-værdier for hvilke y-værdierne skal estimeres; "
"standardværdi er @{known_xs}"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4156
msgid ""
"Let us assume that the cells A1, A2, …, A5 contain numbers 11.4, 17.3, 21.3, "
"25.9, and 40.1, and the cells B1, B2, ... B5 23.2, 25.8, 29.9, 33.5, and "
"42.7."
msgstr ""
"Lad os antage at cellerne A1, A2, …, A5 indeholder tallene 11,4, 17,3, 21,3, "
"25,9 og 40,1, og cellerne B1, B2, ... B5 23,2, 25,8, 29,9, 33,5 og 42,7."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4159
msgid "Then TREND(A1:A5,B1:B5) equals {12.1, 15.7, 21.6, 26.7, 39.7}."
msgstr "Så er TREND(A1:A5,B1:B5) lig med {12,1, 15,7, 21,6, 26,7, 39,7}."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4296
msgid "LOGEST:exponential least square fit"
msgstr "LOGEST:Eksponentiel mindste kvadraters tilpasning"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4298
msgid "known_xs:known x-values; default to an array {1, 2, 3, …}"
msgstr "known_xs:kendte x-værdier; standardværdi er en matrix {1, 2, 3, …}"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4301
msgid ""
"LOGEST function applies the “least squares” method to fit an exponential "
"curve of the form\ty = b * m{1}^x{1} * m{2}^x{2}... to your data."
msgstr ""
"LOGEST-funktionen anvender \"mindste kvadraters\" metode til at tilpasse en "
"eksponentiel kurve af formen\ty = b * m{1}^x{1} * m{2}^x{2}... til dine data."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4305
msgid "LOGEST returns an array { m{n},m{n-1}, ...,m{1},b }."
msgstr "LOGEST returnerer en matrix { m{n},m{n-1}, ...,m{1},b }."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4306
msgid ""
"Extra statistical information is written below the regression line "
"coefficients in the result array.  Extra statistical information consists of "
"four rows of data.  In the first row the standard error values for the "
"coefficients m1, (m2, ...), b are represented.  The second row contains the "
"square of R and the standard error for the y estimate.  The third row "
"contains the F-observed value and the degrees of freedom.  The last row "
"contains the regression sum of squares and the residual sum of squares."
msgstr ""
"Ekstra statistisk information skrives under regressionslinjekoefficienterne "
"i resultatmatrixen. Ekstra statistisk information består af fire rækker af "
"data. I den første række repræsenteres standardfejlværdierne for "
"koefficienterne m1, (m2, ...), b. Den anden række indeholder kvadratet af R "
"og standardfejlen for y-estimatet. Den tredje række indeholder F-observeret "
"værdi og frihedsgraderne. Den sidste række indeholder regressionens sum af "
"kvadrater og residual sum af kvadrater."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4392
msgid "GROWTH:exponential growth prediction"
msgstr "GROWTH:Eksponentiel vækstforudsigelse"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4395
msgid ""
"new_xs:x-values for which to estimate the y-values; defaults to @{known_xs}"
msgstr ""
"new_xs:x-værdier for hvilke y-værdierne skal estimeres; standardværdi er "
"@{known_xs}"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4397
msgid ""
"GROWTH function applies the “least squares” method to fit an exponential "
"curve to your data and predicts the exponential growth by using this curve."
msgstr ""
"GROWTH-funktionen anvender \"mindste kvadraters\" metode til at tilpasse en "
"eksponentiel kurve til dine data og forudsiger den eksponentielle vækst ved "
"at bruge denne kurve."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4402
msgid ""
"GROWTH returns an array having one column and a row for each data point in "
"@{new_xs}."
msgstr ""
"GROWTH returnerer en matrix med én kolonne og en række for hvert datapunkt i "
"@{new_xs}."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4494
msgid ""
"FORECAST:estimates a future value according to existing values using simple "
"linear regression"
msgstr ""
"FORECAST:Estimerer en fremtidig værdi i henhold til eksisterende værdier ved "
"hjælp af simpel lineær regression"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4496
msgid "x:x-value whose matching y-value should be forecast"
msgstr "x:x-værdi hvis tilsvarende y-værdi skal prognosticeres"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4499
msgid ""
"This function estimates a future value according to existing values using "
"simple linear regression."
msgstr ""
"Denne funktion estimerer en fremtidig værdi i henhold til eksisterende "
"værdier ved hjælp af simpel lineær regression."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4501 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4558
#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4611
msgid ""
"If @{known_xs} or @{known_ys} contains no data entries or different number "
"of data entries, this function returns a #N/A error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis @{known_xs} eller @{known_ys} ikke indeholder dataposter eller "
"forskellige antal dataposter, returnerer denne funktion en #N/A-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4503
msgid ""
"If the variance of the @{known_xs} is zero, this function returns a #DIV/0 "
"error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis variansen af @{known_xs} er nul, returnerer denne funktion fejlen "
"#DIV/0!"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4509
msgid "Then FORECAST(7,A1:A5,B1:B5) equals -10.859397661."
msgstr "Så er FORECAST(7,A1:A5,B1:B5) lig med -10,859397661."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4555
msgid "INTERCEPT:the intercept of a linear regression line"
msgstr "INTERCEPT:Skæringspunktet for en lineær regressionslinje"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4560 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4613
msgid ""
"If the variance of the @{known_xs} is zero, this function returns #DIV/0 "
"error."
msgstr ""
"Hvis variansen af @{known_xs} er nul, returnerer denne funktion fejlen "
"#DIV/0!"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4566
msgid "Then INTERCEPT(A1:A5,B1:B5) equals -20.785117212."
msgstr "Så er INTERCEPT(A1:A5,B1:B5) lig med -20,785117212."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4607
msgid "SLOPE:the slope of a linear regression line"
msgstr "SLOPE:Hældningen af en lineær regressionslinje"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4618
msgid "Then SLOPE(A1:A5,B1:B5) equals 1.417959936."
msgstr "Så er SLOPE(A1:A5,B1:B5) lig med 1,417959936."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4659
msgid "SUBTOTAL:the subtotal of the given list of arguments"
msgstr "SUBTOTAL:Subtotalen af den givne liste af argumenter"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4660
msgid ""
"function_nbr:determines which function to use according to the following "
"table:\n"
"\t1   AVERAGE\n"
"\t2   COUNT\n"
"\t3   COUNTA\n"
"\t4   MAX\n"
"\t5   MIN\n"
"\t6   PRODUCT\n"
"\t7   STDEV\n"
"\t8   STDEVP\n"
"\t9   SUM\n"
"\t10   VAR\n"
"\t11   VARP"
msgstr ""
"function_nbr:bestemmer hvilken funktion der skal bruges i henhold til "
"følgende tabel:\n"
"\t1   AVERAGE\n"
"\t2   COUNT\n"
"\t3   COUNTA\n"
"\t4   MAX\n"
"\t5   MIN\n"
"\t6   PRODUCT\n"
"\t7   STDEV\n"
"\t8   STDEVP\n"
"\t9   SUM\n"
"\t10   VAR\n"
"\t11   VARP"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4673
msgid "ref1:first value"
msgstr "ref1:første værdi"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4674
msgid "ref2:second value"
msgstr "ref2:anden værdi"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4676
msgid ""
"Let us assume that the cells A1, A2, ..., A5 contain numbers 23, 27, 28, 33, "
"and 39."
msgstr ""
"Lad os antage at cellerne A1, A2, ..., A5 indeholder tallene 23, 27, 28, 33 "
"og 39."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4677
msgid ""
"Then SUBTOTAL(1,A1:A5) equals 30. SUBTOTAL(6,A1:A5) equals 22378356. "
"SUBTOTAL(7,A1:A5) equals 6.164414003. SUBTOTAL(9,A1:A5) equals 150. "
"SUBTOTAL(11,A1:A5) equals 30.4."
msgstr ""
"Så er SUBTOTAL(1,A1:A5) lig med 30. SUBTOTAL(6,A1:A5) er lig med 22378356. "
"SUBTOTAL(7,A1:A5) er lig med 6,164414003. SUBTOTAL(9,A1:A5) er lig med 150. "
"SUBTOTAL(11,A1:A5) er lig med 30,4."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4749
msgid "CRONBACH:Cronbach's alpha"
msgstr "CRONBACH:Cronbachs alfa"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4750
msgid "ref1:first data set"
msgstr "ref1:første datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4751
msgid "ref2:second data set"
msgstr "ref2:andet datasæt"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4847
msgid ""
"GEOMDIST:probability mass or cumulative distribution function of the "
"geometric distribution"
msgstr ""
"GEOMDIST:Sandsynlighedsmasse- eller kumulativ fordelingsfunktion for den "
"geometriske fordeling"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4848
msgid "k:number of trials"
msgstr "k:antal forsøg"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4849
msgid "p:probability of success in any trial"
msgstr "p:sandsynlighed for succes i et vilkårligt forsøg"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4851
msgid "If @{k} < 0 this function returns a #NUM! error."
msgstr "Hvis @{k} < 0, så returnerer denne funktion en #TAL!-fejl."

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4878
msgid "LOGISTIC:probability density function of the logistic distribution"
msgstr "LOGISTIC:Sandsynlighedstæthedsfunktion for den logistiske fordeling"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4909
msgid "PARETO:probability density function of the Pareto distribution"
msgstr "PARETO:Sandsynlighedstæthedsfunktion for Pareto-fordelingen"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4911
msgid "a:exponent"
msgstr "a:eksponent"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4912 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:5005
msgid "b:scale parameter"
msgstr "b:skalaparameter"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4943
msgid "RAYLEIGH:probability density function of the Rayleigh distribution"
msgstr "RAYLEIGH:Sandsynlighedstæthedsfunktion for Rayleigh-fordelingen"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4945 ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4966
msgid "sigma:scale parameter"
msgstr "sigma:skalaparameter"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4963
msgid ""
"RAYLEIGHTAIL:probability density function of the Rayleigh tail distribution"
msgstr ""
"RAYLEIGHTAIL:Sandsynlighedstæthedsfunktion for Rayleigh-halefordelingen"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:4965
msgid "a:lower limit"
msgstr "a:nedre grænse"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:5001
msgid ""
"EXPPOWDIST:the probability density function of the Exponential Power "
"distribution"
msgstr ""
"EXPPOWDIST:Sandsynlighedstæthedsfunktionen for eksponentiel potensfordeling"

#: ../plugins/fn-stat/functions.c:5007
msgid ""
"This distribution has been recommended for lifetime analysis when a U-shaped "
"hazard function is desired. This corresponds to rapid failure once the "
"product starts to wear out after a period of steady or even improving "
"reliability."
msgstr ""
"Denne fordeling er blevet anbefalet til levetidsanalyse når en U-formet "
"hazardfunktion ønskes. Dette svarer til hurtig fejl når produktet begynder "
"at slides op efter en periode med konstant eller endda forbedret "
"pålidelighed."

